channel.title: I have a semi-fatal error....HELP!
channel.description:
ok so ive benn adding stuff to my server (3 new skills), and i got parseincomingpackets: code too large. I fixed it, then i got one saying i was out of memory. i fixed that now i got this error, and i dont know how to fix it. now im not an expert coderm but i've tried everything i could and nothing worked. so somone please help me. here's the error.
Note: stream.java uses or overrides a deprecated API. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:deprecation for details. ~~~ZymusScape by Zyle |~Enabled~| ~~~ ClientHandler: Accepted from localhost:1102 zymus is signing onto server. [client-1-zymus]: Case 130: 0 [client-1-zymus]: playerCommand: bank [client-1-zymus]: Case 130: 0 [client-1-zymus]: playerCommand: pickup 2949 1 [client-1-zymus]: playerCommand: pickup 1205 1 [client-1-zymus]: Unhandled packet [53, InterFaceId: 129, size=12]: ]01 00 80 35 04 0C 8E 85 0B 0C 8E 31[ [client-1-zymus]: Action Button: 638 [client-1-zymus]: Unhandled packet [53, InterFaceId: 129, size=12]: ]01 00 80 35 04 0C 8E 85 0B 0C 8E 31[ [client-1-zymus]: Action Button: 638
then i get ANOTHER error that says out of memory please help if you can. ~ Zymus ~
